title.narrative: QUALITY MATERNAL/NEONATAL/CHILD HEALTH SERVICES

description.narrative: By 2022, health facilities are equipped for providing quality maternal, neonatal and child health services, including gender responsive adolescent health services., which contributes to Adolescent Health And Nutrition, Child Health, Fast-Track The End Of Hiv/Aids, Fast-Track The End Of Hiv/Aids (Covid), Health And Development In Early Childhood And Adolescence, Immunization, Immunization Services As Part Of Primary Health Care, Immunization Services As Part Of Primary Health Care (Covid), Maternal And Newborn Health, Mental Health And Psychosocial Well-Being, Nutrition Of Adolescents And Women, Strengthening Primary Health Care And High-Impact Health Interventions, Strengthening Primary Health Care And High-Impact Health Interventions (Covid). UNICEF aims to achieve this through Fostering Innovation And Use Of New Technologies, Operational Support To Programme Delivery, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building, Systems Strengthening To Leave No One Behind. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: By 2022,boys and girls aged 0-59 months, adolescents and women (especially those living in the most disadvantaged communities) have access to basic services, use packages of multisectoral high-impact, gender-sensitive interventions (health /HIV, nutrition, WASH) and adopt appropriate behaviours.

description.narrative: En 2021, le renforcement des capacités des prestataires par le coaching et le mentorat, la dotation en équipements, médicaments de 44 nouvelles structures sanitaires des 40communesde convergence, l’approvisionnement en vaccins et matériels de vaccination dans 1,370 structures sanitaires ont permis d’offrir les services de santé maternelle, néonatale et infantile de qualité dans le contexte de la Maladie à Virus Ebola et de la COVID-19. 4,424 nouvelles femmes enceintes dépistées et mises sous ARV sur 4,997 attendues. 89,2% d’enfants de 0-11 mois ont reçu leur troisième dose de penta 3(janvier à octobre)avec un taux d’abandon de 7%. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:02/02/2022
